aving significant implications for the dispute over the importanceof infantry before the fourteenth century. There is also an important article by Richard Abels dealing with the contrasting `cultural determinist' and `scientific' approaches to understanding the mindset of medieval warriors, andthe existence (or not) of a `Western Way of War'. CONTRIBUTORS: RICHARD ABELS, CARROLL GILLMOR, ALDO A. SETTIA, GREGORY D. BELL, RUSSELL MITCHELL, DONALD J. KAGAY, CHRISTOPHER ALLMAND.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMilitary history, MedievalvPeriodicals. 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aCarolingian War-Horse Breeding.  aCommunal Horsemen.  aCuman Warriors.  aFootsoldiers.  aHundred Years War.  aMedieval Warfare.  aMilitary Action.  aPolitics.  aSpanish War-Finance.  aWestern Way of War.1 aAbels, Richard P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbels, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllmand, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBell, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBell, Gregory D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeVries, Kelly, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrance, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGillmor, Carroll, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKagay, Donald J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMitchell, Russ, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMitchell, Russell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRogers, Clifford J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/r